sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Notebook
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP TCP
    participant Worker as Worker Pods<br/>23456/TCP TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 1: PyTorchJob Creation and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate PyTorchJob<br/>TLS 1.2+ Webhook cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation success
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created

    K8sAPI->>Operator: PyTorchJob event<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Services<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Master->>Worker: Distributed training<br/>23456/TCP TCP (plaintext)
    Worker->>S3: Load training data<br/>AWS credentials
    S3-->>Worker: Dataset
    Worker->>S3: Save checkpoints<br/>AWS credentials

    Master->>ModelReg: Register trained model<br/>Bearer Token
    ModelReg-->>Master: Model registered

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 2: Distributed TensorFlow Training

    User->>K8sAPI: Create TFJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate TFJob<br/>TLS 1.2+ Webhook cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation success

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Chief Pod
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Parameter Server Pods

    participant Chief as Chief Pod<br/>gRPC
    participant PS as Parameter Server<br/>2222/TCP gRPC

    Chief->>PS: Gradient updates<br/>2222/TCP gRPC (plaintext)
    Worker->>PS: Gradient updates<br/>2222/TCP gRPC (plaintext)
    Worker->>S3: Save checkpoints<br/>AWS credentials

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 3: MPI-based HPC Training

    User->>K8sAPI: Create MPIJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate MPIJob<br/>TLS 1.2+ Webhook cert

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher Pod
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods

    participant Launcher as Launcher Pod<br/>SSH
    participant MPIWorker as MPI Worker Pods<br/>Dynamic TCP/UDP

    Launcher->>MPIWorker: SSH to workers<br/>22/TCP SSH key auth
    MPIWorker->>MPIWorker: MPI communication<br/>Dynamic TCP/UDP (plaintext)
    MPIWorker->>S3: Load data & save checkpoints<br/>AWS credentials
